onship Game|1949]], [[1960 NFL Championship Game|1960]], [[Super Bowl LII|2017]]\n\n|-\n| Philadelphia Phillies\n| MLB\n| [[1980 World Series|1980]], [[2008 World Series|2008]]\n\n|-\n| Philadelphia 76ers{{efn|group=all|The 76ers franchise also won the [[1955 NBA Finals|1954-55]] title as the Syracuse Nationals}}\n| NBA\n| [[1967 NBA Finals|1966-67]], [[1983 NBA Finals|1982-83]]\n\n|- \n| Philadelphia Flyers\n| NHL\n| [[1974 Stanley Cup Finals|1973-74]], [[1975 Stanley Cup Finals|1974-75]]\n\n|-\n| Philadelphia Warriors\n| NBA\n| [[1947 BAA Finals|1946-47]],{{efn|group=all|The Warriors won the 1947 [[Basketball Association of America|BAA]] Finals. The [[National Basketball Association|NBA]] traces its lineage through its predecessor, the BAA, which was founded in 1946. The BAA merged with the [[National Basketball League (United States)|NBL]] to form the NBA 1949.}} [[1956 NBA Finals|1955-56]]\n\n|-\n| Philadelphia Athletics\n| MLB\n| [[1910 World Series|1910]], [[1911 World Series|1911]], [[1913 World Series|1913]], [[1929 World Series|1929]], [[1930 World Series|1930]]\n\n|-\n| Frankford Yellow Jackets\n| NFL\n| [[1926 NFL season|1926]]\n\n|}\n\n====Championship game/series appearances====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Franchise\n! scope=\"col\" | Season{{efn|group=all|Includes conference championships and post-1900 MLB league pennants.}}\n\n|-\n| Athletics\n| [[1905 Philadelphia Athletics season|1905]]\n\n|-\n| Athletics\n| [[1910 Philadelphia Athletics season|1910]]\n\n|-\n| Athletics\n| [[1911 Philadelphia Athletics season|1911]]\n\n|-\n| Athletics\n| [[1913 Philadelphia Athletics season|1913]]\n\n|-\n| Athletics\n| [[1914 Philadelphia Athletics season|1914]]\n\n|-\n| Phillies\n| [[1915 Philadelphia Phillies season|1915]]\n\n|-\n| Athletics\n| [[1929 Philadelphia Athletics season|1929]]\n\n|-\n| Athletics\n| [[1930 Philadelphia Athletics season|1930]]\n\n|-\n| Athletics\n| [[1931 Philadelphia Athletics season|1931]