organ]] (Up) <br> {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Christina Koch]] (Down) || Delivered [[Expedition 60]]/[[Expedition 61|61]] crew to ISS. || 201 Days\n|-\n| [[Soyuz MS-14]] || [[File:Soyuz-MS-14-Mission-Patch.png|45px]] || N/A || Uncrewed test flight to validate Soyuz for use on [[Soyuz-2.1a]] booster || 14 Days\n|-\n| [[Soyuz MS-15]] || [[File:Soyuz-MS-15-Mission-Patch.png|45px]] || {{Flagicon|RUS}} [[Oleg Skripochka]] <br> {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Jessica Meir]] <br> {{Flagicon|UAE}} [[Hazza Al Mansouri]] (Up) <br> {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Andrew R. Morgan|Andrew Morgan]] (Down) || Delivered [[Expedition 61]]/[[Expedition 62|62]] crew to ISS. || 206 Days (planned)\n|-\n| [[Soyuz MS-16]] || [[File:Soyuz-MS-16-Mission-Patch.png|45px]] || {{Flagicon|RUS}} [[Anatoli Ivanishin]] <br> {{Flagicon|RUS}} [[Ivan Vagner]] <br> {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Christopher Cassidy]] || Delivered [[Expedition 62]]/[[Expedition 63|63]] crew to ISS. || 196 Days (planned)\n|-\n| [[Soyuz MS-17]] || || {{Flagicon|RUS}} [[Nikolai Tikhonov (cosmonaut)|Nikolai Tikhonov]] <br> {{Flagicon|RUS}} [[Andrei Babkin]] <br> {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Steve Bowen]] || Planned to deliver [[Expedition 63]]/[[Expedition 64|64]] crew to ISS. || ~ 200 days (planned)\n|-\n| [[Soyuz MS-18]] || || {{Flagicon|RUS}} [[Sergey Ryzhikov (cosmonaut)|Sergey Ryzhikov]] <br> {{Flagicon|RUS}} [[Sergey Kud-Sverchkov]] <br> {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Kathleen Rubins]] || Planned to rotate future crew to the ISS. || ~ 200 Days (planned)\n|-\n| [[Soyuz MS-19]] || || {{Flagicon|RUS}} [[Oleg Novitsky]] <br> {{Flagicon|RUS}} [[Pyotr Dubrov]] <br> {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Thomas Marshburn]] || Planned to rotate future crew to the ISS. || ~ 200 Days (planned)\n|-\n| [[Soyuz MS-20]] || || {{Flagicon|RUS}} TBA <br> Space Tourist TBA <br> Space Tourist TBA || Planned to ferry one Russian cosmonaut and two [[Space Adventures]] tourists to the ISS. || ~ 10 Days\n|}\n\n== References ==\n\n{{Reflist|30em|refs=\n<ref name=popularmechanics-20160705>{{cite web |url=http://www.popularmechanics.com/space/news/a21668/soyuz-russia-spacecraft-upgrade/ |title=Russia's Workhorse Soyuz Space Taxi Gets a Makeover |last=Zak |first=Anatoly |publisher=NASA Space Flight |date=2016-07-05 |access-date=2016-07-06}}</ref>\n<ref name=energiapr-iss48photo0704>{{cite web |url=http://www.energia.ru/en/iss/iss48/photo_07-04.html |title=Launch vehicle with Soyuz MS spacecraft is on the launch pad |publisher=[[S. P. Korolev Rocket and Space Corporation Energia|Energia]] |date=2016-07-04 |access-date=2016-07-06}}</ref>\n<ref name=nasajsc-ytvsdklArMnCU>{{cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vsdklArMnCU |title=The New, Improved Soyuz Spacecraft |people=Rob Navias |medium=[[YouTube]] |series=Space Station Live |publisher=[[Johnson Space Center|NASA JSC]] |date=2016-07-08 |access-date=2016-07-09 }}</ref>\n<ref name=nkmag-2015241928082>{{cite web |url=http://novosti-kosmonavtiki.ru/mag/2015/2419/28082/ |script-title=ru:\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u043c\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0444\u0438\u043a\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f \"\u0421\u043e\u044e\u0437\u0430\" \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0442 \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0437 \u0433\u043e\u0434 |trans-title=A new version of the Soyuz to flight this year |last=Krasilnikov |first=A. |publisher=Novosti Kosmonavtiki |language=Russian |date=2015 |access-date=2016-07-09}}</ref>\n<ref name=nsf-20160706>{{cite web |url=https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2016/07/russia-crew-upgraded-soyuz-ms-series/ |title=Russia set for Station crew launch in upgraded Soyuz MS-series vehicle |last=Gebhardt |first=Chris |publisher=NASA Space Flight |date=2016-07-06 |access-date=2016-07-06}}</ref>\n<ref name=nsfforum-26410.992797>{{cite web |url=http://forum.nasaspaceflight.com/index.php?topic=26410.msg992797#msg992797 |title=Soyuz-MS spacecraft |work=nasaspaceflight.com |last=Hendrickx |first=Bart |date=2012-12-17 |access-date=2016-07-06}}</ref>\n<ref name=ria-201606301455160339>{{cite web |url=http://ria.ru/science/20160630/1455160339.html |script-